Over the past few months, I’ve dealt with several injuries stemming from 2 sprained ankles. I haven’t been able to move normally and perform to my full capabilities. I’ve genuinely felt depressed as movement is part of my everyday life and career. Things as simple as walking and standing have become problematic, let alone lifting and training. 

The road to recovery has been extremely hard but working with @adamquigley has been absolutely incredible. I noticeably feel better and can move my body more efficiently. Adam emphasizes recovery shouldn’t be solely focused on post-injury, but something you should be mindful of to improve daily wellness. This helps us live and move longer, better, stronger, and healthier. 🙏🏽

While consistency is crucial, monotony can hinder growth. Changing up your workout routine is key to unlocking continuous progress. 🏋🏽‍♂️

Incorporating strength training to your daily fitness regimen not only builds resilience, but transforms your entire fitness journey. Relying solely on familiar exercises can lead to stagnation and reduced motivation. Introducing variety, like embracing strength training, can reignite your passion for fitness and yield better results. Don’t hesitate to step out of your comfort zone and explore new workouts that challenge both your body and mind. 👊🏽

Embrace the change, break plateaus, and elevate your fitness game with us at @ghostbrooklyn!! 🔨 

Interested in training with us? Book a consultation online or shoot us a note at info@ghost.xyz 🔥

Try this CHEST & BACK Workout to sculpt your chest and build your back! @shimonishikawa @ghostbrooklyn 

Working out chest and back together offers a time-efficient approach, appropriate training frequency, balanced agonist-antagonist pairs, and improved work capacity.

Agonist-antagonist pairs are exercise pairings that target opposing sides of the body consecutively. This means you are working 2 opposing muscle groups without any rest in between sets. Incorporating chest and back exercises within the same session allows for the use of agonist-antagonist supersets. 💪🏽 

CHEST & BACK Workout:

1. DB Bench Press
5 x 10 reps

2. Chest-Supported Bench Rows
5 x 8-10 reps

3. Cable Flyes
4 x 15 reps

4. Standing Cable Rope Lat Pushdown
4 x 12-15 reps

5. Weighted Dips
4 x 6-8 reps

6. Weighted Pull-Ups
4 x 6-8 reps

Try this LOWER BODY / Posterior Chain Workout with @elsie !! @ghostbrooklyn 🔥

The Posterior Chain is made up of the glutes, hamstrings, calves, erector spinae, lats, and rear shoulder muscles. It spans the backside of your body and enables crucial movements like standing up, running, and lifting. Integrating posterior chain strength and flexibility exercises into your routine is crucial for athletic performance, back health, and posture. A strong posterior chain enhances your athletic abilities, prevents injuries, and boosts longevity! 🏋🏽‍♂️

It is extremely important to focus on form before adding weights into the mix! When lifting weights, improper technique can seriously hamper your performance and can even result in long term injuries. It restricts your range of motion and hinders strength gains, undermining the benefits of strength training.

Maintaining proper form during exercises reduces the risk of injury / pain, and enhances your performance level!

Women’s Self Defense at @ghostbrooklyn !! 🥊 A very special thank you to @coachjunhlee for leading this seminar! Email Rhys@ghost.xyz if you would like to attend the next one! 📲

Women’s self-defense is crucial for personal safety, empowerment, and deterrence. It empowers women with the skills and confidence to protect themselves, both physically and mentally. It can reduce victimization, promote gender equality, and foster a sense of self-reliance. Additionally, self-defense training enhances physical fitness, mental preparedness, and builds supportive communities among participants. While self-defense is essential, it should be part of a broader strategy to combat violence against women, including education, consent awareness, and creating safer environments.

Coach Jay Lee is an international self defense expert and Krav Maga Specialist and has helped hundreds of students achieve their fitness/training goals in the past year at his own Self Defense school; Korean Tiger Studios. He received his certification in Krav Maga / Counterterrorism in Israel, where he was the Head Striking Coach for one of the largest self defense companies in the country. He has been training for over 20 years and has trained special operations, police officers, professional athletes, and nationally and internationally ranked champions all over the world. He is cornering his fighters almost every other week as his students are active competitors. Outside of martial arts, he has a degree in Medical Health Sciences and Global Health from Cornell University and worked with the #1 ranked hospital in NYC for vaccine development research. He is now dedicated full-time to martial art and fight choreography.
